In the heart of summer's heat,
grasshoppers serenade the sun,
a chorus of life thriving,
a celebration of warmth and light.

Beneath the strong embrace of trees,
the earth feels alive,
a pulse beating in time with the world,
a dance of existence unforgotten.

- Nino Frassica
